				\begin{document}$$v(t + 1) = w \times v(t) + c_{4} \times r_{4} \times \left( {X_{pbest} - X(t)} \right) + \left( {X_{rabbit} (t) - X(t)} \right) + E \times \left| {J \times X_{rabbit} - X(t)} \right|$$\end{document}18X(t+1)=X(t)+v(t+1)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$X(t + 1) = X(t) + v(t + 1)$$\end{document}where v denotes the velocity of each hawk, Xpbest is the personal best position of each hawk, c3 and c4 are the memory factors, r3 and r4 are the random numbers in [0, 1], w represents the inertia weight and is calculated by:19w(t)=winitial-(winitial-wend)×t1+1+t2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
